5.notes: If you're competing on Saturday, I'd recommend the following weekly structure for taper week: Monday - off - Weds - off - off - Competition. You can feel free to adjust around your schedule as well - it's probably better to get the lifts in when you have the time and energy to be present and put focus into the sessions as opposed to cramming it into a busy day to line up with an "ideal" schedule.

Danil and/or myself can help with attempt selection, reviewing openers the week of, and taper modifications as well. Also, there is a meet card & free download in the Discord that can help with planning attempts for competition day, so make sure to check that out.
